```julia
function clean_column(col)
    return Symbol(lowercase(String(col)) |> replace(' ' => '_') |> strip())
end
```

This function takes a `Symbol` or a `String` and returns a `Symbol` with the column name cleaned. It first converts the input to a `String`, then lowercases it, replaces spaces and hyphens with underscores, and finally strips any leading or trailing whitespace before converting back to a `Symbol`.
